-- Bank of Canada Buys C$660 Million in Securities for One Day
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2012-04-20T15:59:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/bank-of-canada-buys-c-660-million-in-securities-for-one-day-1-.html
The  Bank of Canada  bought C$660
million ($666 million) of securities for one day, aiming to keep
overnight lending rates close to its current target of 1
percent.  The central bank increased today’s purchase from an earlier
C$555 million, it said on its website. Today’s move is the
fourth in five days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
